cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on language models for word ordering. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new neural model, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses attention-based sequence-to-sequence models, which are commonly used in neural machine translation, falling under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the model on a large German WMT dataset, which involves text and potentially images, falling under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
